name: Party Sugar Cookies
description: A versatile sugar cookie. Any flavor of gelatin may be used in this recipe. The flavor and color will change depending upon what flavor gelatin you use. You may tint the dough with food coloring, if desired.
ingredients: 1 (3 ounce) package fruit flavored Jell-O® mix #1 cup white sugar #1 cup shortening #3 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #½ teaspoon salt #3 ¼ cups all-purpose flour #1 egg white #¼ cup colored sugar for decoration

name: No Sugar Raisin Cookies
description: These oatmeal raisin cookies do not have any sugar or sugar substitute. Perfect for children, they can eat as many as they want.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups raisins #½ cup peeled, cored and chopped apple #1 cup water #½ cup butter #1 cup all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup quick cooking oats #2 eggs, beaten #¾ cup chopped walnuts

name: Old Lady Cleveland's Gooey Bars
description: Gooey, cream cheese and lemon center. Crispy and nutty top. You have never tasted anything soooo good! The only good thing Old Lady Cleveland ever gave us!
ingredients: 1 (18.25 ounce) package yellow cake mix #½ cup margarine, melted #1 egg #4 cups confectioners' sugar #2 eggs #1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese #1 (18.25 ounce) package lemon cake mix #½ cup chopped pecans

name: High Altitude Banana Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: This recipe is for high altitude and produces a soft, delicious cookie. To adapt for regular altitude, increase baking powder to two teaspoons, and reduce flour to three and one quarter cups.
ingredients: 3 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #¼ teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #1 cup butter, softened #1 cup white sugar #½ cup brown sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup mashed banana #2 cups semisweet chocolate chips

name: Chococonut Chip Cookies
description: I came up with this scrumptious recipe one day, just trying to find a way to use the bag of coconut flakes sitting in the cupboard. It was just a cross between family recipes for cookies and my own special touch of imagination. Well I'm glad that I came up with it as are my family and friends. I hope you enjoy as much as we did.
ingredients: 1 cup butter #1 cup white sugar #½ cup light brown sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 ¼ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #2 cups semisweet chocolate chips #2 cups flaked coconut

name: Doggie Treats I
description: These Doggie Treats are made with whole wheat flour and Cheddar cheese. Sure to turn any dog into your best friend.
ingredients: 1 ¼ cups shredded Cheddar cheese #½ cup vegetable oil #¼ cup beef broth #2 cloves garlic, minced #1 cup whole wheat flour #½ cup all-purpose flour #½ cup cornmeal #¼ cup powdered milk

name: Sandies
description: I found this recipe just lying around so I decided to make it. They are so much fun to make! They taste really good too!
ingredients: 1 cup butter #⅓ cup white sugar #2 teaspoons water #2 teaspoons vanilla extract #2 cups sifted all-purpose flour #1 cup chopped pecans #3 tablespoons confectioners' sugar

name: Pizza-Pan Cookies
description: This is a chocolate-chip cookie in the form of a large pizza! A wonderful substitute for birthday cake too!
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #¾ cup white sugar #¾ cup brown sugar #1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 large eggs eggs #2 ¼ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #¼ teaspoon salt #2 cups semisweet chocolate chips #1 cup chopped walnuts

name: Oatmeal Raisin Cookies VII
description: A chewy oatmeal raisin bar cookie with a hint of cinnamon. If you don't like raisins, candy or chocolate chips can be easily substituted for them.
ingredients: ½ cup butter, softened #¾ cup white sugar #¼ cup brown sugar #1 egg #½ teaspoon vanilla extract #¾ cup self-rising flour #½ teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon ground cinnamon #¼ teaspoon salt #1 ½ cups quick cooking oats #1 cup raisins

name: No Bake Chocolate Oatmeal Cookies
description: These are so yummy, you'd never guess they were vegan!
ingredients: .666 cup maple syrup #¼ cup vegetable oil #5 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #½ cup peanut butter #1 cup rolled oats #1 teaspoon vanilla extract

name: Marbled Cookies
description: Just simply delicious and very easy. You can substitute butterscotch chips or vanilla chips or white chocolate chips for the chocolate chips.
ingredients: 1 cup butter #1 cup white sugar #24 saltine crackers #3 cups semisweet chocolate chips #1 cup finely chopped walnuts

name: Cowboy Cookies III
description: These are yummy. If you can manage to get them to cook just the right way, they aren't crunchy, but soft and the tiniest bit chewy, and melt in your mouth!
ingredients: 2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #1 cup butter, softened #1 cup white sugar #1 cup packed brown sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups rolled oats #1 cup semisweet chocolate chips

name: Chocolate Chip Krispies
description: A chocoholic's dream! Everyone loves the crunch, but no one ever guesses what it is. People can't eat just one.
ingredients: 1 cup unsalted butter #1 ⅓ cups packed light brown sugar #2 eggs #4 teaspoons water #1 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract #2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon salt #4 cups semisweet chocolate chips #2 cups crispy rice cereal

name: Ricotta Cookies III
description: This is a delicious light & fluffy cookie with a hint of lemon in the frosting. The ricotta cheese gives them a heavenly texture.
ingredients: 1 cup butter #2 cups white sugar #2 eggs #16 ounces ricotta cheese #2 teaspoons vanilla extract #4 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #½ cup milk #½ teaspoon butter #½ teaspoon shortening #4 cups confectioners' sugar #1 tablespoon lemon extract #½ cup colored candy sprinkles

name: Peanut Butter Balls VIII
description: Mom made these for us for as long as I can remember. They are a great in between meals or after school. Easy to make and great tasting too! Yes, they even have bran (the good for you stuff) in them. Enjoy!
ingredients: 2 cups peanut butter #2 ½ cups whole bran cereal #2 cups powdered milk #1 ½ cups raisins #¾ cup honey

name: Fravioli
description: Deep fried raviolis filled with a sweet ricotta cheese filling. These are a very original treat to add to your repertoire.
ingredients: 2 ¼ cups all-purpose flour #2 tablespoons white sugar #¼ teaspoon salt #⅜ cup shortening #2 eggs #2 tablespoons dry white wine #1 ½ cups ricotta cheese #1 egg #¼ cup white sugar #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #4 cups vegetable oil for frying

name: Coconut Gumdrop Cookies
description: These oatmeal cookies are chewy and sweet. The flavors of coconut, gumdrops and pecans are blended to perfection.
ingredients: 1 cup shortening #1 cup white sugar #1 cup packed brown sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #¼ teaspoon salt #1 cup flaked coconut #2 cups rolled oats #1 cup chopped pecans #1 cup gumdrops, chopped

name: Cottage Cheese Cookies
description: Chocolate cookies with cottage cheese and nuts mixed in. These cookies are very chocolate-y and moist. Very good!
ingredients: 2 cups shortening #3 ½ cups white sugar #4 eggs #4 teaspoons vanilla extract #5 ½ cups all-purpose flour #2 teaspoons baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #1 cup unsweetened cocoa powder #2 cups cottage cheese #1 cup chopped pecans #½ cup confectioners' sugar

name: Graham Cracker Icing
description: My mother used to make graham cracker cookies for us all the time. We usually just used left-over frosting from a cake. Her recipe was really good, only we usually had chocolate frosting just because that was our favorite. Just leave out cocoa for vanilla frosting.
ingredients: ½ cup margarine #1 egg #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #4 cups confectioners' sugar #2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder #¼ cup milk

name: Lollipop Sugar Cookies
description: Sugar cookies on a stick! These cookies make great party favors or centerpiece bouquets. Decorate with sprinkles or frosting. You will need two dozen craft sticks for this recipe.
ingredients: 1 cup shortening #½ cup white sugar #½ cup brown sugar #½ teaspoon vanilla #1 egg #2 cups all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt

name: Dream Bars II
description: This is an old time South Dakota recipe. Cocoa is an optional ingredient. This recipe is made in two parts.
ingredients: ½ cup butter #½ cup brown sugar #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #3 eggs, beaten #1 ½ cups brown sugar #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #¼ cup all-purpose flour #¼ cup unsweetened cocoa powder (Optional)#1 teaspoon baking powder #¼ teaspoon salt #1 ½ cups flaked coconut #1 cup chopped walnuts

name: Portuguese Walnut Squares
description: These are chewy walnut bars made by my Titia Albertin in Sao Miguel, Azores. They have a wonderful flavor that comes from Port wine.
ingredients: ½ cup butter, softened #¾ cup brown sugar #1 egg #½ teaspoon vanilla extract #2 tablespoons milk #2 tablespoons port wine #1 cup chopped walnuts #⅜ cup all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon baking powder #2 tablespoons port wine #1 cup confectioners' sugar #1 tablespoon butter, softened #1 tablespoon port wine #2 drops red food coloring

name: Italian Fig Cookies II
description: Not a dainty cookie - it is a hearty fig-filled delight!
ingredients: 2 ½ cups all-purpose flour #⅓ cup white sugar #¼ teaspoon baking powder #½ cup shortening #2 tablespoons butter #½ cup milk #1 egg, beaten #1 ½ cups dried figs #¾ cup golden raisins #¼ cup slivered almonds #¼ cup white sugar #¼ cup hot water #¼ teaspoon ground cinnamon #1 pinch ground black pepper

name: Chocolate Chip Eggnog Balls
description: This a quick and easy, no bake cookie, all will just love it!!
ingredients: 2 (3 ounce) packages cream cheese, softened #4 cups sifted confectioners' sugar #1 tablespoon heavy cream #1 teaspoon brandy #½ teaspoon salt #¼ teaspoon ground cinnamon #⅛ teaspoon ground nutmeg #½ cup miniature semisweet chocolate chips #1 ¼ cups finely chopped pecans

name: Danish Pastry Apple Bars II
description: Better than apple pie, and can be served warm. These go very quickly when served with other bar cookies.
ingredients: 2 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon salt #1 cup butter #1 egg yolk #⅔ cup cold water #1 cup cornflakes cereal #10 apples - peeled, cored and sliced #¾ cup white sugar #2 teaspoons ground cinnamon #½ cup confectioners' sugar #1 tablespoon milk #½ teaspoon almond extract

name: Oatmeal Raisin Toffee Cookies
description: The toffee candy bar bits make this cookie VERY addictive! A great twist on an old-fashioned cookie.
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #1 cup brown sugar #½ cup white sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #3 cups rolled oats #1 cup raisins #1 cup crushed toffee candy

name: Doggie Treats II
description: These are chicken and Cheddar cheese flavored treats for man's best friend. Give a package of treats to a favorite dog. Include a cutter and a copy of the recipe.
ingredients: 1 cup rolled oats #⅓ cup margarine #1 cup boiling water #¾ cup cornmeal #1 tablespoon white sugar #2 teaspoons chicken bouillon granules #½ cup milk #1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese #1 large egg #2 ½ cups whole wheat flour

name: Very Chocolate Cookies
description: These chocolaty chocolate chip cookies are very good. Everyone I know begs me to make them for them.
ingredients: 1 ¼ cups margarine, softened #2 cups white sugar #2 eggs #2 teaspoons vanilla extract #2 cups all-purpose flour #¾ cup unsweetened cocoa powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #2 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips

name: Coffee Liqueur Raisin Cookies
description: This is a wonderful, chewy, just a little different oatmeal cookie. I have made them with many variations and all of them good. They taste the best if the raisins soak in the coffee liqueur overnight.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups raisins #½ cup coffee flavored liqueur #1 cup shortening #2 cups packed brown sugar #3 eggs #½ cup milk #3 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #2 ½ cups rolled oats #1 cup chopped walnuts (Optional)#1 cup white chocolate chips (Optional)

name: Best Ever Chocolate Chip Cookies II
description: Chocolate chip cookies are the best, but these are the best ever! The brown sugar is what makes these cookies so soft and chewy!
ingredients: 1 cup butter, melted #2 cups brown sugar #2 eggs #2.666 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #2 cups semisweet chocolate chips

name: Oatie Chip Cookies
description: The secret to this chocolate chip cookie's great texture is oat flour made out of regular oatmeal. Since it makes a large batch I usually freeze some of the dough in cookie-sized drops. The frozen cookies need to be baked about 2 minutes longer and seem to be even stickier in texture and more chewy.
ingredients: 2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #2 ½ cups rolled oats #1 cup butter, softened #1 cup white sugar #1 cup brown sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips #1 cup chopped pecans

name: Stroopwaffels II
description: Dutch cookie with caramel syrup between two thin cookies. Absolutely delicious! I lived in Holland for a year and fell in love with these cookies. I was so happy to finally find a recipe! These are made using a pizzelle iron.
ingredients: 1 ¼ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 pinch salt #2 eggs #¾ cup white sugar #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 teaspoons lemon extract #⅓ cup butter, melted #1 cup white sugar #1 tablespoon corn syrup #1 teaspoon lemon juice #6 tablespoons heavy cream

name: Grandma Orcutt's Date Cookies
description: This is an old recipe that is easy to make. These are delicious slice and bake cookies with chunks of dates and nuts. Keep a roll in your freezer in case of unexpected company. Very good served WARM!!
ingredients: 1 cup shortening #2 cups brown sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #3 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon cream of tartar #2 tablespoons milk #1 cup chopped dates #1 cup chopped walnuts

name: Mississippi Tea Cakes
description: This is my mother's recipe, her mother's recipe, and so on... Basic, simple, down-home and delicious!! My grandmother's advice is to enjoy warm with a big glass of ice-cold milk!!! Poor folks' heaven!!!
ingredients: ½ cup butter, softened #1 cup white sugar #1 egg #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #½ teaspoon baking soda #¼ cup buttermilk

name: Popcorn Macaroons
description: This is a wonderful macaroon recipe! We recommend a sugar substitute that is heat stable using a sweetener such as sucralose or acesulfame potassium.
ingredients: 2 cups popped popcorn #3 egg whites #½ teaspoon baking powder #¼ teaspoon salt #¼ teaspoon cream of tartar #2 tablespoons granulated artificial sweetener

name: No-Bake Peanut Butter Candy
description: A really quick and simple candy recipe. My pre-schoolers make this recipe during circle time. They love it!
ingredients: 1 cup peanut butter #1 cup corn syrup #1 ¼ cups milk powder #1 ¼ cups confectioners' sugar

name: Pumpkin Cookies VII
description: These cookies are very soft and moist with a cake-like texture and my family always loves them. They are great any time of the year.
ingredients: 1 cup butter flavored shortening #1 cup white sugar #1 egg #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup canned pumpkin puree #2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #1 (3.4 ounce) package instant vanilla pudding mix #1 (16 ounce) container cream cheese frosting

name: Double Chocolate Biscotti II
description: Delicious rich, dark, semi-sweet double chocolate biscotti that you can make at home for a fraction of the cost of store bought biscotti, and they even taste much better. This recipe has been modified with egg substitute.
ingredients: 1 cup white sugar #¼ cup olive oil #¼ cup margarine #¾ cup egg substitute #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 ⅛ cups unsweetened cocoa powder #2 teaspoons baking powder #1 (5 ounce) milk chocolate candy bar, chopped

name: Whoopie Pies VII
description: Little hands just love these chocolate sugar cream-filled pies!! Whoopie!!
ingredients: 2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #¼ teaspoon salt #⅓ cup unsweetened cocoa powder #1 cup white sugar #1 egg #½ cup vegetable oil #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #¾ cup milk #½ cup milk #2 ½ tablespoons all-purpose flour #½ cup shortening #½ cup white sugar #½ teaspoon salt #1 tablespoon vanilla extract

name: Cucidati II
description: This takes some time to prepare, but is well worth the work. I looked years for this recipe for my father-in-law. After many tries, I found the one that reminded him of his grandmother's Christmas cookies.
ingredients: 1 pound dried figs #1 cup raisins #2 ½ teaspoons orange zest #½ pound chopped walnuts #1 cup honey #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips #1 cup orange marmalade #2 ½ cups sifted all-purpose flour #½ cup white sugar #2 ½ teaspoons baking powder #½ cup shortening #2 eggs, beaten #¼ cup milk #½ teaspoon vanilla extract

name: New Brunswick Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: A nice treat from southern New Brunswick in Canada. Very soft chocolate chip cookies with a hint of cinnamon.
ingredients: ½ cup butter, softened #½ cup crunchy peanut butter #1 cup white sugar #1 cup brown sugar #2 eggs #¼ cup milk #1 teaspoon cream #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 ¾ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #½ teaspoon ground cinnamon #2 ½ cups rolled oats #½ cup milk chocolate chips

name: Philippine Butter Cookies
description: These are also called Puto Seco. This is a tasty, butter cookie that is complimented with a cup of tea. The cornstarch in the recipe makes them light and crunchy.
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #1 cup white sugar #3 eggs #3 ⅔ cups cornstarch #1 teaspoon cream of tartar #1 teaspoon baking powder

name: Perfect Gluten-Free Peanut Butter Cookies
description: A healthy, gluten free version of perfect peanut butter cookies.
ingredients: ½ cup gluten free, casein free margarine #½ cup brown sugar #½ cup white sugar #1 egg #½ cup salted natural peanut butter #½ teaspoon baking soda #1 cup soy flour #¼ cup tapioca flour #¼ cup potato flour

name: Soft Oatmeal Cookies
description: These oatmeal cookies are very moist with a good flavor. Add a cup of raisins or nuts if you desire.
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #1 cup white sugar #1 cup packed brown sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #1 ½ teaspoons ground cinnamon #3 cups quick cooking oats

name: Creme de Menthe Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: This is a great adult version of an old classic! The Creme de Menthe turns the cookies a pleasing shade of green too!
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #1 cup brown sugar #¾ cup white sugar #2 eggs #2 tablespoons creme de menthe liqueur #3 cups all-purpose flour #¾ teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #3 cups mint chocolate chips

name: Red Wine Sesame Biscuits
description: These biscuits are crunchy and not too sweet. I like to use a soft red wine for these delicious sesame coated treats.
ingredients: 2 ½ cups all-purpose flour #⅓ cup white sugar #2 ½ teaspoons baking powder #½ teaspoon salt #1 egg #½ cup vegetable oil #⅓ cup red wine #1 egg white #2 tablespoons sesame seeds, toasted

name: Peppermint Ammonia Cookies
description: This is a recipe for cookies that my grandma used to make when I was a child. They are very light cookies.
ingredients: ½ cup butter, softened #1 ½ cups white sugar #1 cup heavy cream #3 eggs, beaten #⅛ cup boiling water #1 ½ tablespoons bakers' ammonia #½ teaspoon peppermint oil #4 ½ cups all-purpose flour #2 ½ teaspoons baking powder

name: Half and Halfs
description: I came up with this recipe when I couldn't decide whether I wanted chocolate chip or double chip cookies so I came up with a way to have both! These cookies are half plain chocolate chip and half chocolate chocolate chip.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #¼ teaspoon baking soda #1 pinch salt #½ cup butter, softened #¼ cup white sugar #½ cup brown sugar #1 egg #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup milk chocolate chips #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #¼ teaspoon baking soda # salt #¼ cup unsweetened cocoa powder #½ cup butter, softened #½ cup brown sugar #½ cup white sugar #1 egg #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup milk chocolate chips

name: Crunchy Munchies
description: This recipe is very easy to memorize and it makes great use of peanut butter! You may need to use a candy thermometer for this recipe.
ingredients: 1 cup corn syrup #½ cup peanut butter #3 cups toasted oat cereal

name: Anise Cookies III
description: These anise cookies are versatile and delicious. Oil can be used in place of margarine for a lower fat version. Any type of nuts can also be used in place of the walnuts. These elegant twice baked cookies are perfect for company.
ingredients: 5 eggs #2 cups white sugar #2 cups margarine, softened #1 teaspoon salt #1 ½ tablespoons baking powder #6 cups all-purpose flour #1 cup finely chopped walnuts #2 tablespoons anise seed

name: Graham Cracker Bars
description: These are a sweet graham cracker crumb bar with coconut and a milk chocolate topping. An easy, quick, yet simply delicious bar recipe...you have to try it! :)
ingredients: 2 cups graham cracker crumbs #2 cups flaked coconut #¼ cup margarine, melted #1 (14 ounce) can sweetened condensed milk #4 (1.55 ounce) bars milk chocolate candy

name: Ammonia Cookies
description: This old fashioned peppermint cookie uses baker's ammonia for the leavening. Baker's ammonia can be purchased at pharmacies and drugstores. Ice with a simple confectioners' glaze that has been flavored with peppermint if desired.
ingredients: 2 ½ cups white sugar #½ cup butter, softened #3 eggs #1 ½ cups sour cream #½ cup milk #1 teaspoon peppermint extract #½ teaspoon salt #2 teaspoons bakers' ammonia #3 cups all-purpose flour

name: Applesauce Oatie Cookies
description: These chewy oatmeal cookies are full of nuts, raisins, and chocolate chips. This is a family favorite cookie recipe. We have been making them for 50 years
ingredients: 1 ¾ cups quick cooking oats #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #½ teaspoon ground nutmeg #½ cup butter, softened #1 cup packed brown sugar #½ cup white sugar #1 egg #¾ cup applesauce #1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips #1 cup raisins #1 cup chopped walnuts

name: Birds' Nests
description: Make cookies that look like bird nests! Pretty for school spring celebrations or Easter. You can use egg-shaped candies in lieu of the jellybeans, too.
ingredients: 3 cups crispy rice cereal #1 cup flaked coconut #⅓ cup corn syrup #½ cup brown sugar #¾ cup peanut butter #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #40 jellybeans

name: Chocolate Chip Coffee Cookies
description: An old fashioned chocolate chip cookie that has been spiked with a coffee liqueur. You'll love these cookies!
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #1 cup brown sugar #¾ cup white sugar #2 egg, beaten #3 tablespoons coffee-flavored liqueur #3 cups all-purpose flour #¾ teaspoon baking soda #¾ teaspoon salt #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #3 cups milk chocolate chips

name: Chocolate Fudge Cookies
description: This recipe is so easy to make, and yields delicious chocolaty cookies.
ingredients: 1 (18.25 ounce) package devil's food cake mix #2 eggs #½ cup vegetable oil #1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips

name: Cinnamon Pecan Cookie Bars
description: These bar cookies are crunchy, lightly sweet and full of cinnamon flavor.
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #¼ cup white sugar #1 egg yolk #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups all-purpose flour #4 teaspoons ground cinnamon #1 egg white #1 cup chopped pecans #2 tablespoons confectioners' sugar

name: Cream Cheese Bars II
description: These are an easy, fast and delicious bar. Great for showers, parties or just a good snack for home. My husband loves these!
ingredients: 2 (8 ounce) packages cream cheese, softened #1 cup white sugar #1 egg yolk #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 (8 ounce) packages refrigerated crescent rolls #¼ cup white sugar #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon

name: Currant Nut Drop Cookies
description: A delicious soft cookie with brown sugar frosting. A long time family favorite.
ingredients: ½ cup hot water #1 cup dried currants #1 cup shortening #2 cups brown sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #3 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #1 teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #1 cup buttermilk #½ cup chopped walnuts #6 tablespoons butter #¼ cup hot water #½ teaspoon vanilla extract #4 cups confectioners' sugar

name: Empire Biscuits
description: This shortbread cookie is a traditional Scottish recipe. These are round cookies sandwiched with jam and topped off with a delicious icing and a cherry.
ingredients: 2 cups butter, softened #1 cup white sugar #4 cups sifted all-purpose flour #1 cup raspberry preserves #24 maraschino cherries #8 cups confectioners' sugar #½ cup milk

name: Lemon Chocolate Drop Cookies
description: These cookies have just the right amount of everything to equal a delicious cookie ! Lemon, spices, and chocolate chips, topped off with a tangy lemon glaze. My friend and I got together and made them because we wanted to bake and couldn't find a recipe we liked so we made these and they were great !
ingredients: 1 cup all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #¼ teaspoon ground cloves #1 teaspoon baking powder #½ cup butter, softened #½ cup white sugar #¼ cup vegetable oil #½ cup milk #¼ cup lemon juice #2 tablespoons lemon zest #½ cup semi-sweet chocolate chips #½ cup confectioners' sugar #2 tablespoons lemon zest #¼ cup water

name: Nana's Tea Cakes
description: These sugar cookies are very soft and fluffy for those of us who like them chewy, not hard or crisp. Try substituting strawberry flavoring for the vanilla!
ingredients: 1 cup shortening #2 cups white sugar #3 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #5 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #½ cup milk

name: Strawberries
description: Unique! Beautiful cookies, really dress up a cookie tray.
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #1 cup white sugar #2 eggs, beaten #8 ounces chopped pitted dates #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup sifted all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon salt #1 cup finely chopped almonds #2 ½ cups crispy rice cereal #½ cup red decorator sugar #1 (4.5 ounce) tube prepared green decorating icing

name: Orange Sugar Cookies
description: Easy to make, but tastes great. This orange cookie holds it's shape well and can be used with figured boards or cookie molds and stamps. Dust with confectioners' sugar after baking for an elegant finish.
ingredients: 1 cup shortening #2 cups white sugar #3 eggs #1 tablespoon orange zest #⅜ cup orange juice #1 tablespoon vanilla extract #5 ½ cups all-purpose flour #2 teaspoons baking powder #1 teaspoon salt

name: Moist Persimmon Cookie
description: This is a soft moist spicy cookie. The persimmon fruit lends its sweetness and color to this simple cookie. Any type if nuts may be used for this and you may prefer to leave out the raisins.
ingredients: 2 persimmons #½ cup shortening #1 cup white sugar #1 egg #2 cups all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon salt #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #½ teaspoon ground cloves #½ teaspoon ground nutmeg #1 cup chopped walnuts #1 cup raisins

name: Peanut Butter Bars VI
description: These peanut buttery cornflake bars are chewy and sweet. They are the best bars I have ever eaten.
ingredients: ¼ cup brown sugar #½ cup corn syrup #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup peanut butter #3 cups crushed cornflakes cereal

name: Peanut Butter Cookies VII
description: These cookies are great; they are extremely moist and peanut buttery.
ingredients: ½ cup shortening #½ cup peanut butter #1 cup white sugar #½ teaspoon vanilla #1 egg #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #¼ teaspoon salt

name: Blondie Caramel Heaven
description: The greatest brownie/blondie I have ever eaten. Addicting and delicious. I also like top them with a fluffy white frosting.
ingredients: 10 ounces individually wrapped caramels, unwrapped #½ cup evaporated milk #1 (18.25 ounce) package yellow cake mix #½ cup evaporated milk #¾ cup butter, melted #¾ cup milk chocolate chips

name: Tiny Fudge Tarts
description: This cookie is like a fudge-filled shortbread.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #¼ teaspoon salt #½ cup butter, softened #3 tablespoons water #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #¼ cup butter, softened #1 egg yolk #½ cup white sugar #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #¼ cup unsweetened cocoa powder #½ cup flaked coconut

name: Caramel Heavenlies
description: These bars are easy to make, chewy and delicious. They are almost too rich to be a cookie.
ingredients: 16 graham crackers #2 cups miniature marshmallows #¾ cup butter #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #¾ cup brown sugar #2 cups sliced almonds #2 cups flaked coconut

name: Cat Poop Cookies III
description: A realistic shocker of a cookie. These look like cat poop and are served in a tidy litter box setting. Mix and match the additions of chocolate or butterscotch chips, ramen noodles (roundworms), coconut (tapeworms), corn or peanuts depending on what effects you want to achieve.
ingredients: ½ cup honey #.666 cup butter #1 egg #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups whole wheat flour #⅓ cup unsweetened cocoa powder #1 (32 ounce) package wheat and barley nugget cereal (e.g. Grape-Nuts™)

name: Brownies IV
description: Chocolaty brownies topped with a rich semisweet chocolate glaze. Serve with ice cream or milk.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups white sugar #1 ½ cups butter, softened #4 eggs #2 teaspoons vanilla extract #1 ¾ cups all-purpose flour #1 cup unsweetened cocoa powder #6 (1 ounce) squares semisweet chocolate #2 tablespoons butter

name: Orange Date Pinwheel Cookies
description: The tang of the orange and sweetness of the dates combine to produce a rich, wonderful cookie.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups chopped pitted dates #¼ cup white sugar #1 pinch salt #¾ cup orange juice #¾ cup water #1 teaspoon orange zest #⅔ cup chopped pecans #3 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 ½ teaspoons baking powder #¼ teaspoon baking soda #¾ teaspoon salt #¾ cup butter, softened #½ cup white sugar #1 cup brown sugar #2 eggs #1 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract #2 teaspoons orange zest

name: Absolutely Sinful Chocolate Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: This recipe was given to me by my grandmother 10 years ago. They were always a HUGE hit at work pig-outs and now my family loves them! A wonderful soft cookie that is incredibly chocolaty.
ingredients: 2 ½ (1 ounce) squares unsweetened chocolate #½ cup butter #2 cups all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon baking powder #¼ teaspoon salt #1 ¼ cups white sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #⅔ cup sour cream #2 cups semisweet chocolate chips

name: Whole-Wheat Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: Everybody raves over these -- they have a richer flavor than ordinary chocolate chip cookies! This is for people with access to freshly-ground flour; it's just not the same with store bought or all white flour. Pecans can be used in place of the walnuts.
ingredients: ¾ cup margarine #1 cup white sugar #1 cup light brown sugar #1 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract #2 eggs #2 cups sifted whole wheat pastry flour #1 cup all-purpose flour #¾ teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #2 cups semisweet chocolate chips #½ cup chopped walnuts (Optional)

name: Tyler's Raspberry Thumbprints with White Chocolate Glaze
description: I made these once for my boyfriend Tyler who is of very discriminating taste. Now he begs me to make them!!!
ingredients: ½ cup butter, softened #½ cup sour cream #1 cup white sugar #2 tablespoons milk #2 eggs #2.666 cups all-purpose flour #2 cups rolled oats #1 teaspoon baking soda #5 ounces white chocolate, chopped #.666 cup raspberry preserves #1 tablespoon butter #½ (1 ounce) square white chocolate #1 cup confectioners' sugar #2 tablespoons milk

name: Turtle Cookies III
description: Easy recipe and fun for the kids. Chocolate cookies that are made on a waffle iron. The squares make them look like little turtles. These cookies are great frosted with your favorite white frosting.
ingredients: 2 cups all-purpose flour #½ cup unsweetened cocoa powder #1 ½ cups white sugar #1 pinch salt #4 eggs, beaten #.666 cup margarine, melted #1 teaspoon vanilla extract

name: Applesauce Brownies II
description: A plain cake-like brownie, moist with great chocolate taste. Easy to make.
ingredients: ½ cup shortening #2 (1 ounce) squares unsweetened chocolate #1 cup white sugar #2 eggs, beaten #½ cup applesauce #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup sifted all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon baking powder #¼ teaspoon baking soda #¼ teaspoon salt

name: Butter Sprinkles
description: This is a rich butter cookie that is decorated with the sprinkles of your choice. They are also good with frosting.
ingredients: 1 cup butter #1 cup white sugar #1 cup confectioners' sugar #1 cup canola oil #½ teaspoon vanilla extract #2 eggs #4 ¼ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon cream of tartar #1 teaspoon salt #¼ cup colored candy sprinkles

name: Almond Chocolate Coconut Cookies II
description: These cookies are easy to make and delicious.
ingredients: 1 cup butter #1 ½ cups white sugar #1 ½ cups brown sugar #4 eggs #4 teaspoons vanilla extract #4 ½ cups all-purpose flour #2 teaspoons baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #5 cups semisweet chocolate chips #2 cups flaked coconut #2 cups chopped almonds

name: Anise Overnight Cookies
description: Anise overnight cookie. Drop cookie onto greased cookie sheet and bake the next day. These are traditional in our family. Delicious with coffee! Anise oil can be found in drugstores or at a candy supplier.
ingredients: 3 eggs #1 ⅛ cups white sugar #¼ teaspoon anise oil #1 ¾ cups all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon baking powder #½ teaspoon salt

name: ANZAC Biscuits with Almonds
description: This is a great variation of a traditional Australian biscuit.
ingredients: 2 cups quick cooking oats #1 ¾ cups all-purpose flour #½ cup sliced almonds #1 cup white sugar #1 cup melted butter #1 teaspoon baking soda #2 tablespoons golden syrup #2 tablespoons boiling water

name: Blondies I
description: Soft, golden cookies packed with white chocolate chips, macadamia nuts, and my secret ingredient, a touch of coconut.
ingredients: ½ cup butter, softened #½ cup shortening #¾ cup white sugar #½ cup packed brown sugar #1 egg #½ teaspoon vanilla extract #1 ¾ cups self-rising flour #2 cups white chocolate chips #½ cup chopped macadamia nuts #⅓ cup flaked coconut

name: Brown Sugar Drops
description: Tasty little drop cookies made with buttermilk and brown sugar. A rewarding treat.
ingredients: 1 cup shortening #2 cups packed brown sugar #2 eggs #½ cup buttermilk #3 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon salt

name: No Bake Cookies VI
description: No-Bake Cookies made with instant chocolate milk mix (not baking cocoa).
ingredients: 2 cups white sugar #½ teaspoon salt #½ cup butter #½ cup milk #½ cup peanut butter #3 cups rolled oats #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #½ cup powdered chocolate drink mix

name: Sausage Pasta
description: This is a super easy recipe to throw together and, with the addition of different vegetables, can make lots of variations.
ingredients: ¾ pound pasta #1 tablespoon olive oil #1 pound spicy Italian sausage #1 onion, chopped #4 cloves garlic, minced #1 (14.5 ounce) can chicken broth #1 teaspoon dried basil #1 (14.5 ounce) can diced tomatoes #1 (10 ounce) package frozen chopped spinach #½ cup grated Parmesan cheese

name: Garlic and Ham Spaghetti
description: This is a wonderful and quick dinner. I have never not been asked for the recipe when I serve it to friends. Don't be discouraged by the number of ingredients... you can add or delete any items you wish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, toss with olive oil and serve with French bread, if desired. Toss in some artichoke hearts if you'd like.
ingredients: 8 ounces spaghetti #5 tablespoons butter #3 cloves garlic, chopped #1 onion, chopped #16 ounces fresh mushrooms, sliced #1 (16 ounce) package frozen chopped broccoli #1 (6 ounce) can black olives, drained #12 slices ham, chopped

name: Chicken Half Moons
description: This yummy homemade stuffed pasta can be served a la carte or with a sauce. It makes an excellent meal or side dish.
ingredients: 1 skinless, boneless chicken breast half #1 onion, chopped #½ cup cubed Cheddar cheese #2 ½ cups all-purpose flour #3 eggs #1 cup water #1 egg #1 tablespoon water

name: Spaghetti Al Amatraciana
description: A spicy Italian Pasta dish where you can vary the amount of red pepper to make this dish as spicy as you like it. Top with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Buon Appetito!
ingredients: ¼ pound thinly sliced pancetta bacon, chopped #1 onion, chopped #1 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes #1 (14.5 ounce) can crushed tomatoes #¼ cup white wine #½ pound uncooked spaghetti # salt and pepper to taste

name: Spaghetti Casserole III
description: My Mom has been making this for years. The recipe calls for ketchup and cheddar cheese but can be made with traditional tomato sauce and your favorite Italian cheese.
ingredients: 1 pound spaghetti #1 pound lean ground beef #1 onion, chopped #1 green bell pepper, chopped #1 clove garlic, minced #1 ½ cups ketchup #1 teaspoon dried oregano # salt and pepper to taste #1 ½ cups shredded Cheddar cheese

name: Calabrese Style Spaghetti
description: Noodles with garlic, butter and grated Italian cheese. Serve with crunchy bread sticks and salad, if desired.
ingredients: 1 (6 ounce) package spaghetti #½ cup butter #2 tablespoons minced garlic #1 cup grated Romano cheese

name: Tortellini a la Carbonara
description: A rich, creamy sauce with bacon and tortellini pasta. Tortellini means 'little twists' in Italian and is rumored to have been shaped after Venus's navel.
ingredients: 3 cups spinach tortellini #3 egg yolks #4 cups heavy whipping cream #1 cup grated Parmesan cheese #1 pound bacon

name: Suz's Vegetable Manicotti
description: Lower in fat but very tasty vegetable manicotti. Great with a little bit of foccacia and a salad.
ingredients: 6 manicotti shells #2 red bell pepper, cut into 1 inch pieces #2 large portobello mushrooms #1 (32 ounce) container part-skim ricotta cheese #2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese #1 egg # salt and pepper to taste #½ teaspoon Italian seasoning #½ teaspoon garlic powder #2 cups spaghetti sauce

name: Fettuccine with Garlic Herb Butter
description: This is wonderful! Try as much or as little of the fresh herbs to suit your tastes. Serve with freshly grated Parmesan cheese and some warm bread, if desired.
ingredients: 6 ounces dry fettuccini pasta #1 teaspoon butter #1 clove garlic, minced #1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley #1 tablespoon chopped fresh basil #1 tablespoon chopped fresh marjoram (Optional)#1 tablespoon chopped fresh thyme (Optional)#1 tablespoon butter #⅛ teaspoon salt #1 pinch ground black pepper
